a london jewelry dealer was identified as the 
person who paid 913 million for the largest diamond ever to be 
sold at auction a sothebys spokeswoman said 
laurence graff purchased the 8591carat pearshaped diamond by 
telephone during tuesdays auction spokeswoman jennifer brown said 
wednesday 
the sale set a record for any gem sold at auction she said 
the diamond which was perfectly cut and flawless was part of 
an auction that brought 36 million a record for a jewelry sale in 
the united states 
the auction included gems belonging to the late clare boothe 
luce a former congresswoman and ambassador to italy 
also wednesday christies announced the sale of a 5259 carat 
diamond ring for 78 million the highest price ever paid per 
carat at auction said spokeswoman lily zimmerman 
she said 132000 was paid per carat by a private saudi arabian 
collector bidding by telephone 
</TEXT>
