<DOCNO> AP880421-0006 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
on the other side of the ledger push improved business 
opportunities for blacks by persuading corporations to sign 
covenants promising jobs and franchises to minorities often 
after push threatened or carried out boycotts of a companys 
product 
from the start on christmas 1971 jackson vowed the group would 
picket vote and if necessary engage in civil disobedience to 
achieve its goals 
williams now a member of the atlanta city council recalled 
jackson had quit as head of a similar group operation breadbasket 
an arm of the southern christian leadership conference after 
clashing with sclc leaders over expenditures and jacksons 
independent streak 
jackson built push into a network with chapters in 32 cities 
taking in 168 million from 1975 to 1986 the last year for which 
state financial records were filed 
he also used the push platform to take on the administrations of 
several presidents and the city hierarchy of chicago on a range of 
issues from us policy in central america to contracts for 
minorityowned businesses 
pushs saturday meetings are part of chicagos political 
landscape mixing the gospel flavor of a southern church revival 
with jacksons stirring speeches on the days hot issues 
from the push pulpit jackson pressured companies such as 
burger king and cocacola to sign minority opportunity compacts 
jesse was instrumental in making a lot of opportunities 
available by that i mean distributorships getting blacks placed 
in jobs in chain stores said dempsey travis a chicago 
businessman and jackson supporter 
push officials have long been secretive about the groups 
sources of money other than to say it is supported by individual 
memberships that now cost 20 a person and donations from 
businesses 
some of the corporations that signed covenants with push also 
contributed money to help sponsor its annual convention or other 
activities coors brewery for example gave 20000 last year to a 
major push scholarship fundraising event in chicago 
in 1977 jackson broadened pushs mission by starting pushexcel 
to get innercity youths to study harder he spoke in packed school 
gymnasiums nationwide with students joining in his trademark 
chant i am somebody 
after jackson fired up the students pushexcel worked with 
local school officials to set up special clubs and programs to help 
keep the youths motivated 
but federal auditors later contended that government money 
received from 1979 to 1982 went for such layouts as 211 for music 
and flowers for a 1979 press party in los angeles 650 for 
christmas cards purchased for a related organization 28 for 
funeral flowers and 15 for a parking ticket 
the government has referred pushexcels 12 million debt to 
the justice department for collection 
as of now we havent been able to resolve it said justice 
spokesman amy brown 
pushexcel dramatized jacksons strengths and weaknesses said 
ernest house an education professor who has just finished writing 
a book about jackson and the studentmotivation program 
jesse had a lot of very good ideas he has trouble carrying 
them through that has been his problem said house who is 
director of the policy studies laboratory at the university of 
colorado at boulder 
they went through three or four directors one right after the 
other and this was part of his difficulty in administering the 
program house said 
by 1986 pushexcels revenues which peaked at 26 million in 
1980 had dropped to 209071 and the group ended the year with a 
15 million debt including the money owed to the government 
operation push wasnt much better off it started 1986 with a 
339056 deficit but took in enough money to reduce the debt to 
84914 by the end of the year according to its annual report 
filed with the state 
the rev willie barrow pushs national executive director did 
not return repeated telephone calls asking for information about 
the organizations current financial status 
frank watkins jacksons longtime aide and spokesman said he 
understood the group had succeeded this year in nearly erasing its 
deficit 
although jackson was pushs driving force his supporters say he 
shouldnt be blamed for organizational problems in areas delegated 
to subordinates jackson himself has said he didnt get involved in 
mechanical details 
if there was anything sloppy about jesses management it was 
that he could not afford paid competent people to deal with the 
various functions of accounting and management of government 
programs said bishop hh bookins a leader in the african 
methodist episcopal church and a jackson supporter 
jesses main thrust was at raising funds to keep the 
organization afloat so it was impossible for him to be a handson 
manager of things he said 
jackson supporters point to the success of his 1988 presidential 
campaign as evidence he can recruit able people to assist him 
leon davis who worked as pushs national executive director in 
1972 said he sees a different jackson today 
from the time i worked with jesse it seems to me he has grown 
tremendously and his campaign points out one thing he has 
delegated authority 
</TEXT>
