<TEXT>
a measure extending the deadline for illegal 
aliens to apply for amnesty faces a difficult fight in the senate 
and a possible presidential veto after clearing the house by a 
narrow margin 
the 213201 house vote wednesday would move the deadline from 
may 4 to nov 30 the extension would represent the first change in 
the landmark immigration law signed by president reagan in november 
1986 
but the immigration and naturalization service issued a warning 
late wednesday to potential applicants that they should heed the 
current may 4 deadline 
ins is concerned that this misguided legislation will create 
confusion among potential applicants and cause them to delay filing 
beyond the may 4 cutoff date the service said in a statement it 
said legalization offices will remain open on may 4 until midnight 
to process applications and that aliens should continue to expect 
that the last date to apply will be may 4 
the immigration law enacted in 1986 was finely tuned legislation 
that carefully balanced a legalization program for illegal aliens 
with penalties for employers who knowingly hire undocumented 
workers 
the narrow margin of wednesdays vote demonstrated that amnesty 
for those who came to this country illegally remains an emotional 
issue in 1986 the house approved the amnesty program as part of 
the immigration bill by only seven votes 
the extension is opposed by sen alan k simpson rwyo the 
chief senate author of the 1986 law and other conservatives 
the immigration law is a delicately balanced bill that uses a 
carrot and stick approach to stop illegal aliens from pouring 
across us borders 
aliens who came to the united states illegally but have lived 
here continuously since before jan 1 1982 were given one year to 
apply for temporary residency as the first step toward permanent 
status the 12month deadline is may 4 
on the enforcement side the law established severe fines for 
employers who knowingly hire undocumented workers 
those favoring the extension argue the immigration and 
naturalization service reacted too slowly at the onset of the 
amnesty period and did not get out the word to the immigrant 
communities to apply for temporary residency 
in addition many illegal aliens were thought to fear appearing 
at an office of the ins the agency that is also in the business of 
deporting those here illegally 
in fact the law prohibits the ins amnesty employees from 
sharing their records with enforcement agents 
those opposing the amnesty extension in the house were basically 
the same members who never liked the idea they said that aliens 
who refused to come forward were simply procrastinators and that 
the carefully structured bill should not be changed to accommodate 
them 
with the deadline approaching the chief senate advocate of the 
extension sen edward m kennedy dmass plans to have a vote 
scheduled quickly in that chamber he is chairman of the senate 
judiciary immigration subcommittee and sponsored the chambers 
extension proposal 
if the bill should get through the senate there could be 
additional problems at the white house 
the commissioner of the ins alan c nelson and office of 
management and budget officials have already said they would 
recommend a presidential veto if the bill reaches reagans desk 
simpson commented wednesday our numbers are right on target 
with the projections we used when we passed the bill i do not 
honestly see a need or justification for extending the signup 
period 
during house debate the chief sponsor of the extension rep 
romano l mazzoli dky said 12 million aliens have applied for 
the general amnesty program and 729000 have received temporary 
residency cards another 400000 have applied for a separate 
agricultural amnesty program that is not affected by the extension 
legislation 
before the final vote the house approved by voice vote an 
amendment designed to cut down on fraud during any extension period 
the house also defeated 167246 an amendment that would have 
only accepted applications after may 4 from aliens who could 
demonstrate good cause for missing the deadline 
</TEXT>
