and means committees were unable to agree on the measures cost 
the senate placed the states cost at about 550 million and the 
house estimated it as high as 12 billion 
dukakis presented figures wednesday showing the states share of 
the plan would rise from 345 million this fiscal year to 1954 
million in fiscal 1991 
the states share is expected to drop to 1627 million in 
fiscal 1992 according to the governors figures but dukakis and 
dunham said state costs beyond fiscal 1989 are hard to estimate 
because they will depend on how many employers decide to offer 
health plans as a result of the law 
