<TEXT>
the capitals worst dust storm in 36 years shut 
down beijings airport for several hours thursday while pedestrians 
used surgical masks and scarves to protect themselves from the 
swirling yellow soil 
the storms began april 2 and have continued intermittently 
since sometimes limiting visibility to a few hundred yards and 
turning the beijing sky already gray from coal dust to a chalky 
yellow 
the last time beijing had such bad weather was 1952 said li 
tingfu of the beijing meteorological bureau 
high winds carrying tons of the soil called loess swirl into 
beijing every spring from the arid plateaus northwest of the 
capital 
the storms have lessened in recent years due to antierosion 
measures such as planting thousands of trees to form a green 
wall north of the city but a lack of rain in inner mongolia and 
gansu province in northwestern china aggravated the problem 
the airport has been forced to close at least twice due to poor 
visibility cars buildings and sidewalks were coated with fine 
dust which also seeped into homes and offices 
</TEXT>
