tennis star ivan lendl on thursday won a major 
battle in his fight to play for the us olympic team this summer 
when a skeptical house subcommittee voted to give the czech native 
immediate us citizenship 
the measure which even proponents had given little chance of 
passage earlier this year was approved without opposition and sent 
to the house judiciary committee 
subcommittee approval likely will lead to easy passage by the 
full house said rep bruce a morrison dconn a member of the 
panel and chief sponsor of the bill 
but the legslation still would face serious obstacles in the 
senate where sen edward m kennedy dmass chairman of the 
