of attitude on olympic citizenship bills 
last year mazzoli outlined a new rule of his judiciary 
subcommittee on immigration refugees and international law that 
viewed private immigration bills as an extraordinary remedy 
available only to assist aliens with unusual problems and where 
extreme hardship can be demonstrated it noted that the panel 
