get a fullview picture of his mouth 
fitzwater explained that the white house has xray machines that 
take pictures of part of the mouth but does not have the larger 
machine that pans the entire mouth area 
the spokesman identified reagans dentist as navy cmdr dr 
james judkins he said the president has not had any complaint 
about his teeth 
the last time reagan visited the hospital was in january when 
he underwent his annual checkup for colon cancer 
it is the first time reagan has gone to bethesda for dental work 
reagan who traveled to springfield mass on thursday to 
deliver a speech on ussoviet relations appeared in good spirits 
upon his return to the white house in the late afternoon he 
smiled waved and gave journalists a thumbsup signal but 
refused to answer questions 
reagan went to bethesda naval hospital jan 15 for a fourhour 
examination to check against the recurrence of colon cancer 
he has had regular checkups every january and june since he 
underwent successful colon cancer surgery in july 1985 
the january test showed no renewal of cancer and no growths he 
was proclaimed by hutton at the time to be in excellent health 
except for the last checkup in january doctors have discovered 
and removed small fleshy growths known as polyps from reaans 
colon in each instance the growths turned out to be benign 
reagan turned 77 in february and is the oldest man to be 
