a new federal government with 
fewer departments and a drastically reduced staff was appointed 
thursday in a move to tighten the belt on czechoslovakias 
bureaucracy 
the official ctk news agency said the new 20member government 
was appointed by president gustav husak the changes however were 
proposed by the communist party leadership at a recent meeting 
the previous 26member government resigned wednesday one day 
after parliament rubberstamped a communist party central committee 
decision to merge five ministries into two 
in czechoslovakia changes in government are decided by the 
party leadership 
lubomir strougal remains premier in the new government which 
has six deputy premiers instead of ten there had been some 
speculation that strougal might be replaced 
the new government now has ten ministries three less than 
previously 
times were never easy for governments strougal said but 
these are the most difficult times 
we know what we want but at the same time we must count on 
many unexpected phenomena which we shall have to solve both in 
economic and social development as well as in internal and foreign 
policy where more activity and initiative is needed on our part 
strougal said 
czechoslovakia has adopted the rhetoric of reform over the past 
year but has proceeded cautiously in making changes like those 
carried out in the soviet union under mikhail s gorbachev 
husak who was replaced as party leader in december by milos 
jakes said each minister is to look critically at the area he is 
responsible for 
the governments of the czech and slovak republics also were 
reorganized reducing their ministries by four and three 
respectively 
the shuffle apparently is designed to streamline government 
bureaucracy and spur the countrys economy 
the communist party daily rude pravo said the staffs of the 
federal and republican governments are to be cut by about 30 
percent rude pravo said thousands of people would be fired 
through the reorganization of state administration 
however it said no one would be left without a job 
the process must be aimed primarily at ensuring the growth of 
quality and performance of the managing aparatus and at a good and 
effective use of the released workers primarily in places and 
professions where manpower has been lacking so far ctk quoted 
rude pravo as saying 
former deputy premier ladislav gerle now heads a newly created 
