which authorizes 4 billion for star wars 600 million less than 
the senate subcommittee voted thursday 
rep les aspin dwis chairman of the house armed services 
committee says he expects the full house to approve the 4 billion 
figure after a fight by liberals who want to reduce it more and 
conservatives who want to raise it 
