for 1986 on total income of 348594 
bushs tax bill amounted to 28 percent of his total income in 
1987 down from the 33 percent he paid in 1986 showing that he as 
president reagan and many other americans benefited from the 
sweeping taxlaw changes that took effect for 1987 taxes 
bushs income included his 112633 salary as vice president and 
2048 in additional reimbursment from the government 
his biggest chunk of outside income came from the blind trust he 
and his wife set up when he took office totaling 169600 
including 26075 in capital gains 31264 in interest and 
