plane ended up 320 miles off course because the cockpit and flight 
data recorders were never recovered but aviation experts theorize 
that incorrect data was punched into the computerized navigation 
system before the plane took off from anchorage 
if the judge dismisses the case the airline would only be 
liable for 75000 per passenger under international aviation 
conventions but the plaintiffs are seeking to collect far greater 
amounts by holding the airline liable for punitive damages 
