when terence knox signed on to play sgt zeke 
anderson in cbs vietnam war series tour of duty it sounded 
like a dream job a starring role in a network show shot on 
location in beautiful hawaii 
its not what its cracked up to be its work said knox on 
a recent visit to drizzly new york 
i hasten to say that what we go through is nothing compared to 
what the veterans went through in real warfare but i can at least 
appreciate it a little bit at least a peeping toms perspective on 
being away from home in a hot place where it rains a lot and where 
you dont really see civilians 
civilians for knox and the rest of the cast and crew are the 
tourists who stay at the same honolulu hotel there is no 
fraternizing 
people come in waves of like two weeks in hawaii so theres 
no meaningful relationship to be struck up here joked the young 
and single knox especially when people are in a zany kind of 
