<TEXT>
in the 1800s the story goes immigrants coming 
to america believed the streets were paved with gold nowadays it 
is foreign retailers who are arriving on these shores in search of 
their fortunes 
they are lured by the size of the us market and the american 
passion for foreign styles and goods several are already reporting 
success 
we could get a large slice of the apple by selling in 
america said sophie mirman who helped introduce the sock shop a 
chain of british hosiery stores to this country 
the most prominent of the new arrivals is campeau corp the 
canadian concern bought out allied stores corp in 1986 and is in 
the process of taking over federated department stores inc 
to help finance its purchase of federated campeau is selling 
allieds brooks brothers chain to another foreign retailer marks 
and spencer plc of britain 
meanwhile the australian developer hooker corp moved into 
retailing with the purchase last year of the bonwit teller b 
altman and sakowitz chains 
buying an american company is not the only way to get here some 
smaller companies are striking out on their own sock shop is among 
them so are fil a fil la sweaterie and tricots caroll apparel 
retailers from france 
a foreign presence in the us retailing industry is nothing 
new in 1973 batus inc the us arm of britains bat industries 
plc swept in with the purchase of saks fifth avenue and the 
nowclosed gimbels chain 
and the fashionable streets of cities like new york washington 
palm beach and los angeles have been graced for years by names such 
as gucci courreges and yves st laurent 
but what is different about many of these latest arrivals is 
they are appealing to a larger and different market segment many 
offer moderatelypriced merchandise giving more consumers a chance 
to buy and wear clothes with foreign labels 
with such prices the new transplants have enormous 
development potential in this market said charles aug whose 
company garrickaug associates store leasing inc scouts foreign 
retailers and helps them set up shop here 
many of the retailers are drawn to the united states in hopes of 
equaling the success of the italian retailer benetton aug said 
benetton has grown to 760 stores in the united states out of 
more than 4500 worldwide since the first us store with its 
nowfamiliar bright green sign opened in manhattan in 1979 said 
sally fischer a spokeswoman for the italian retailer 
said aug the rapid growth of benetton generated the interest 
of the other european merchants to come over here and start 
moving 
benetton stores are operated under licensing agreements with the 
italian company the stores sell only benetton fashions and buy 
the clothes from benetton ms fischer said 
other retailers break into the us market through franchises 
in which they can profit from an american operation without having 
the expense and problems of opening and managing stores 
printemps a denver fashion retailer is a franchisee of au 
printemps a french department store chain the us store which 
opened in november operates autonomously of its namesake but 
turns over to au printemps a percentage of its sales said frank 
ball president of the american company 
the denver store sells french fashions but is americanized 
for practicality said ball weve used the name but the 
denver store is not a reflection of the store in france 
