stores in manhattan in december and were delighted with the way 
theyre going said ms mirman chairman of the company 
because of its size the united states was one of several 
markets sock shop wanted to explore ms mirman said the company 
hopes to open nine more outlets this year and eventually expand 
beyond new york 
the retailers generally get some assistance from american 
advisers or brokers before setting up shop ms mirman said sock 
shops entry into the united states was facilitated by a minority 
stockholder who lived in new york la sweaterie was brought into 
the american market through a joint venture with david genser the 
companys president here 
unlike many other foreign retailers la sweaterie did not try 
new york first opening instead in the boston area where genser 
lives the retailer now has 29 stores in the united states 
including several in california 
the weakness of the dollar since 1985 has helped some 
foreigners aug said explaining installation costs would be a 
fraction of what it would have cost them a few years ago 
but the lower dollar can be a doubleedged sword 
its cheaper to set up shop but thats offset by the fact 
that the market for goods at these price points does not grow 
when the dollar is buying less said max garelick president of 
rodier usa the american arm of the french clothing chain rodier 
genser agreed it has hurt us he said of the dollars 
decline all of our clothes are made in france and become more 
expensive as the us currency slides 
one way to fight the impact of currency fluctuations is to 
become a more american company benetton has started manufacturing 
some of its merchandise in rocky mount nc ms fischer said 
but the style will remain something thats italian and french 
what european companies have to offer she said 
