the us dollar rose marginally against the 
japanese yen in morning trading on friday while stock prices 
posted moderate gains in light activity 
the dollar opened at 12429 yen almost unchanged from its close 
thursday of 12430 and edged up slightly at midmorning it was 
changing hands at 12440 yen 
an exchange dealer at a major commercial bank in tokyo said a 
lack of fresh news kept the dollar stable in early foreign exchange 
activity trading also was uneventful on overseas markets which 
close before the tokyo exchange opens 
on the tokyo stock exchange the nikkei stock average of 225 
selected issues down 3593 points on thursday gained 5134 to 
close the morning session at 2687950 
overnight stability on overseas stock markets and the 
relatively stable yendollar exchange rates combined to fuel a 
moderate advance said seiichiro kita of daiwa securities co a 
major japanese brokerage 
kita said some market participants were taking a cautious 
position because of uncertainty over prospects for us interest 
rates but otherwise the markets firmness will continue 
