<DOCNO> AP880421-0325 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
usg corp said wednesday it would allow its 
stockholders to decide whether the company should drop its 
poisonpill takeover defense which is a major impediment to a 
texas groups 163 billion takeover attempt 
but usg said the offer was conditioned on the willingness of the 
investor group desert partners lp to extend the deadline for 
its takeover bid a provision criticized by desert partners 
desert partnerss offer of 42 a share cash for 85 percent of 
usgs stock has been spurned as inadequate by the company a maker 
of building materials 
usgs poison pill seeks to make a hostile takeover prohibitively 
expensive by allowing management to issue more shares if a bidder 
acquires more than 20 percent of the companys stock 
desert partners which owns about 98 percent of usgs 
outstanding stock repeatedly has called on usg to rescind the 
poison pill and issued a statement that it was pleased usg was 
putting the issue to a shareholder vote 
however the group criticized usgs request for it to extend its 
offer through june 16 from its current expiration on friday desert 
partners said usg provided no assurance that it would refrain from 
taking other defensive moves during that time 
the partnership reiterated that it is willing to negotiate all 
aspects of its offer including price the statement concluded 
efforts to reach desert partners for further comment beyond the 
statement were unsuccessful and a message was not immediately 
returned after business hours late wednesday 
usg announced late wednesday that it would submit the 
poisonpill question to a special shareholder vote on june 6 if 
desert partners extended its tender offer to june 16 
if 85 percent of usg shareholders voted to rescind the poison 
pill usg would do so by june 16 stated robert j day usg 
chairman and chief executive officer 
the usg board has previously concluded that the desert 
partners offer is wholly inadequate coercive and not in the best 
interests of usg and its stockholders day said 
we believe that by submitting the rights plan to a stockholder 
vote in a free noncoercive atmosphere the stockholder vote will 
support the boards conclusion he said 
desert partners which is controlled by oilmen jack brown and 
cyril wagner jr of midland texas also is trying to circumvent 
the poison pill by waging a proxy fight to fill six spots on usgs 
15member board of directors at the companys may 11 annual meeting 
</TEXT>
